column1: How many employees does your company or organization have?
column2: Is your employer primarily a tech company/organization?
column3: Is your primary role within your company related to tech/IT?
column4: Does your employer provide mental health benefits as part of healthcare coverage?
column5: Do you know the options for mental health care available under your employer-provided health coverage?
column6: Has your employer ever formally discussed mental health (for example, as part of a wellness campaign or other official communication)?
column7: Does your employer offer resources to learn more about mental health disorders and options for seeking help?
column8: Is your anonymity protected if you choose to take advantage of mental health or substance abuse treatment resources provided by your employer?
column9: If a mental health issue prompted you to request a medical leave from work, how easy or difficult would it be to ask for that leave?
column10: Would you feel more comfortable talking to your coworkers about your physical health or your mental health?
column11: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health issue with your direct supervisor(s)?
column12: Have you ever discussed your mental health with your employer?
column13: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health issue with your coworkers?
column14: Have you ever discussed your mental health with coworkers?
column15: Have you ever had a coworker discuss their or another coworker's mental health with you?
column16: Overall, how much importance does your employer place on physical health?
column17: Overall, how much importance does your employer place on mental health?
column18: Was your employer primarily a tech company/organization?
column19: Did your previous employers ever formally discuss mental health (as part of a wellness campaign or other official communication)?
column20: Did your previous employers provide resources to learn more about mental health disorders and how to seek help?
column21: Was your anonymity protected if you chose to take advantage of mental health or substance abuse treatment resources with previous employers?
column22: Would you have felt more comfortable talking to your previous employer about your physical health or your mental health?
column23: Would you have been willing to discuss your mental health with your direct supervisor(s)?
column24: Did you ever discuss your mental health with your previous employer?
column25: Did you ever discuss your mental health with a previous coworker(s)?
column26: Did you ever have a previous coworker discuss their or another coworker's mental health with you?
column27: Overall, how much importance did your previous employer place on physical health?
column28: Overall, how much importance did your previous employer place on mental health?
column29: Have you had a mental health disorder in the past?
column30: Have you ever sought treatment for a mental health disorder from a mental health professional?
column31: Do you have a family history of mental illness?
column32: Have your observations of how another individual who discussed a mental health issue made you less likely to reveal a mental health issue yourself in your current workplace?
column33: How willing would you be to share with friends and family that you have a mental illness?
column34: Would you be willing to bring up a physical health issue with a potential employer in an interview?
column35: Are you openly identified at work as a person with a mental health issue?
column36: Overall, how well do you think the tech industry supports employees with mental health issues?
